	(text "Not sure whether to use 2mm or 2.5mm pitch for JST connectors.\nOriginal PCB used 2mm, even though datasheet of encoder says\n2.5mm for the GA37-520. Used 2.5mm pitch for now.\n\nJST XH: 2.5mm pitch\nJST PH: 2.0mm pitch"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 103.378 154.178 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "461ee7b1-2728-44b4-b8d1-f8d03f4444ab")
	)
	(text "Voltage divider is fast enough (RC LP):\n6000 RPM = 100 rps\n100 rps x 12 ppr = 1200 pps\n4 x 1200 = 4800 Hz (1/T encoding)\nEncoder output rise/fall time: 300-1500 ns\nESP32 S3 typical pin capacitance: 2 pF\nTraces, cables, connectors: ~20 pF\nT = R x C = 5k1 x 22pF = 112.2ns => OK"
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 48.768 99.822 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.27 1.27)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "913d562a-2b8a-4ac1-9db2-5e52a08e492f")
	)
